# Make screenshot
# Sleep is required because for some reason, scrot detects the key release
# as a sign to take screenshot and then xclip cannot find the saved file.
# 0.2 seconds is the most optimal time between giving time to release
# PrtSc key and not feeling too long to react
"sleep 0.2 && ${HOME}/Scripts/prtsc.sh"
	Print

"sleep 0.2 && ${HOME}/Scripts/prtsc.sh full"
    Alt + Print
